Photoabsorption edge model.  
</SYNOPSIS>
	<DESC>
<PARA>
A phenomenological photoabsorption edge model as a function of energy:
</PARA>

<PARA>
<EQUATION>
f'(x) = f(x)
</EQUATION>
</PARA>

<PARA>
if x &lt; E_b, and
</PARA>

<PARA>
<EQUATION>
f'(x) = f(x) exp[-A(x/E_b)^-3]
</EQUATION>
</PARA>

<PARA>
otherwise.
</PARA>

<PARA>
Or, as a function of wavelength:
</PARA>

<PARA>
<EQUATION>
f'(x) = f(x)
</EQUATION>
</PARA>

<PARA>
if x &gt; lambda_b, and
</PARA>

<PARA>
<EQUATION>
f'(x) = f(x) exp[-A(x/lambda_b)^3]
</EQUATION>
</PARA>

<PARA>
otherwise.
</PARA>

